Javier Fernndez

Field: Economic of Education, Applied Microeconomics, Efficiency Analysis, Regional Economy, Web Scraping.
Education: Tesista Magister en Economa, Universidad Adolfo Ibez.
Contact: javier.fernandezch@edu.uai.cl
web site http://cepr.uai.cl/equipo/javier-fernandez/
About: Javier Fernndez is a student and thesist student of the Master in Economics at the Adolfo Ibez University. Since December 2017, he has been a research associate at CEPR, where he works on education and efficiency issues. His thesis of magister studies the relation between the municipal management in education and the efficiency in quality of this. His subjects of interest are economic development, microeconometrics, regional economy, data visualization and web scraping. Since August 2018, Javier is a part-time professor at the Business School.
